title: U.S. - Infant mortality rate 1990 to 2018
yAxis: Infant mortality rate per thousand live births
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Infant mortality rate per thousand live births. In total the number of data points it has is 29.
Overall Infant mortality rate per thousand live births has decreased over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 1990 and 1991.
The highest Infant mortality rate per thousand live births, of value 9.4 was reached at Year 1990
Minimum Infant mortality rate per thousand live births about 5.6 was reached at Year 2018
